u0632|date=9 April 2019|website=@SkyNewsArabia_B|language=ar|access-date=9 April 2019}}</ref> It was reported that the airport closed on 8 April, after it was bombed by the GNA, and also that the Misrata Airport, located 200&nbsp;km (125 miles) to the east down the coast,<ref name=\"reutersapril9look\" /> was the nearest airport for Tripoli residents.<ref name=\"reutersapril9look\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.antiwar.com/2019/04/08/libyan-unity-govt-bombs-then-recaptures-tripoli-airport/|title=Libyan Unity Govt Bombs, Then Recaptures Tripoli Airport|first=Jason|last=Ditz|date=9 April 2019}}</ref> A GNA spokesperson claimed that the GNA air force carried out several raids against LNA supply lines.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/AlkhaleejOnline/status/1115631316463173633|title=\u0648\u0631\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0622\u0646 {{!}} \u0627\u0644\u0645\u062a\u062d\u062f\u062b \u0628\u0627\u0633\u0645 \u0642\u0648\u0627\u062a \u062d\u0643\u0648\u0645\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0648\u0641\u0627\u0642 \u0627\u0644\u0648\u0637\u0646\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064a\u0628\u064a\u0629: \u0633\u0644\u0627\u062d\u0646\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u062c\u0648\u064a \u0646\u0641\u0630 \u063a\u0627\u0631\u0627\u062a \u0639\u062f\u064a\u062f\u0629 \u0643\u0634\u0641\u062a \u062e\u0637\u0648\u0637 \u0625\u0645\u062f\u0627\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0639\u062f\u0648|last=\u0623\u0648\u0646\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0646|first=\u0627\u0644\u062e\u0644\u064a\u062c|date=9 April 2019|website=@AlkhaleejOnline|language=ar|access-date=9 April 2019}}</ref> LNA and GNA forces engaged in a battle for control over the road to Tripoli Int'l Airport and Qasir bin Gashir detention center, which at that time housed over 600 people.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/mannocchia/status/1115618415123812353|title=Clashes in Qasr Bin Gashir, airport road. Recording from Qasir bin Gashir detention center, A. sent me few minutes ago. There are 600 people inside \u2013 man, women and children \u2013 who need to be evacuated.|